The paper presents a method for solving the transshipment problem and single-source shortest paths problem in undirected graphs with polynomially bounded integer edge weights using a tailored gradient descent algorithm. This involves techniques from optimization, graph algorithms, and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.NE (Networks and Economics). Additionally, the paper also discusses streaming and communication complexity models, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
